verbose_text: Similarly, oxygen levels appear to have some effect on methanogens, which were not observed in either the uppermost horizons within bromeliad tanks or throughout the water column in artificial catchments (i.e., amber bottles), both of which had elevated O 2 levels (2-8 ppm O 2), compared to the bottommost methanogen dominated horizons within bromeliad tanks (< 1 ppm O 2).
